review_blob: Tiny 237ml can from a Spermarket in Lefkoa, Turkish occupied north of Cyprus.  Rated as "Amsterdam Navigator SHOT". Smooth and slightly sweetish beginning. Grain, sweetish body, but easy to drink. Hints of sweetish grain, round and sessionable though. No bitterness, smooth and grainy-sweetish finish. Interesting!
Can from a Russian shop in Cyprus . Grainy weak beginning. Sessionable, grainy and breads sweetish. Strange grainy aftertaste with not much bitterness.
Can from a touristy shop in Cyprus . Grainy sweetish beginning. Easy to drink, no bitterness. The body is weak, sweetish hints, neutral grainy sweetish aftertaste. Only in the sun refreshing!

Can from a supermarket in Cyprus  (cant remember whether it was Carrefour or  ). The beer starts grainy with a malty sweetness. No hints of bitterness, round and sweetish. Grainy hints, a bit of metal. Bitter strange sweetish bready aftertaste. Not great.

500ml-Bottle for 6.50TL from Snake off-licence in Lefkoa, Turkish occupied northern part of Cyprus . The beer starts as neutral as the Golden Ale. But if you add some of the thick and massive sediment, the beer becomes smooth with muddy coffe hints. Very strange - tastes a bit like a Turkish/Greek coffee with all of the coffee-grounds in the cup. Sessionable, full in aroma. Hints of dry caramel, chocolate, round and smooth. Not bad!

500ml-Bottle for 6.50TL from Snake off-licence in Lefkoa, Turkish occupied northern part of Cyprus . Grainy smooth nose. The beer starts mild-neutral. Very neutral with hints of Golden Ale in the background. Easy to drink but with a lack of flavour. Moderate bitter aftertaste, fresh, sessionable with a moderate sweetness.

Bottle from a Spermarket in Girne, Turkish occupied northern part of Cyprus .  The beer smells grainy-sweetish. The beginning is neutral watery and grainy sweetish. Not much aroma in total. Grainy sweetish aftertaste, round and mild. Sessionable, but a bit grainy-sweetish.

50cl bottle for 3.55TL from a Spermarket in Girne, Turkish occupied north of Cyprus .  Nice golden colour, grainy nose. The beer starts grainy with some sweetness. No bitterness, round and refreshing. Moderate sweetish, nice refreshing with grainy hints.

Bottle from a Spermarket in Girne, Turkish occupied North of Cyprus . Sweetish lemonade beginning. Refreshing and sweetish. Hints of Tequila in the back, fruity-sweetish with hints of beer. Nice Shandy!

50cl bottle from a Spermarket in Girne (Kyrenia), Turkish occupied northern part of Cyprus.  Smooth and a bit dusty grainy beginning. Easy to drink, refreshing with a nice subtle yeasty dusty background. Full in taste, not too sweetish, no bitterness. Refreshing and round. Nice!

1l bottle from a Spermarket in Girne (Kyrenia), Turkish occupied northern part of Cyprus.  Grainy neutral beginning. The beer starts smooth but a bit watery. Easy to drink and refreshing with not too much depth or bitterness. Hints of sweetness, light, sessionable!

pint from a beach bar, Nissi Bay, Cyprus . Refreshing brew. Slightly malty, hints of grain. Very refreshing with not much bitterness. Hints of metal in the aftertaste, but round and fresh. Nice refreshing stuff.
Can from Carrefour in Cyprus . Smooth grainy beginning. Malty with moderate sweetish hints. The aftertaste is a bit grainy, not much bitterness and refreshing!
Bottle from a shop in Nicosia, Cyprus . Smooth grainy beginning. Fresh and easy to drink with malty-grainy hints. Crisp with a nice but neutral bitterness. Sessionable!
Can from a shop in Nicosia, Cyprus . Neutral grainy beginning. Worth, bread, strange card board. Unround and sweetish.
Bottle (4.2%) from Carrefour in Nicosia, Cyprus . Neutral grainy beginning. Smooth, fresh, easy to drink. Fresh, smooth, nice and easy to drink. Session beer.

Bottle from Snake off-licence in Lefkoa, Occupied Turkish North of Cyprus . Dry grainy beginning. Hints of smooth caramel, roasted grain. Extremely drinkable. Very smooth. Milk chocolate, great fresh. The aftertaste is smooth, slightly malty with a great smooth malty chocolate aftertaste. Fascinating for a beer from a Turkish country...

Can from a corner-shop in Lefkoa, Occupied Turkish North of Cyprus . Sweetish-grainy beginning. Grainy, slightly sweetish, not too deep. Slightly alcoholic, easy to drink, Slightly grainy. Not much bitterness, slightly sticky. Interesting...
Bottle from a corner-shop in Lefkoa, Occupied Turkish North of Cyprus . Grainy sweetish beginning. Corn, sweetish grain. Easy to drink but no depth or bitterness. Interesting!

Can (Efes Xtra Shot) from a corner-shop in Lefkoa, Occupied Turkish North of Cyprus . Sweetish grainy aroma. Alcohol, sticky, dried fruit on a very alcoholic basis. Interesting sticky. Strange stuff, but not too bad.
Bottle from a corner-shop in Lefkoa, Occupied Turkish North of Cyprus . Smooth grainy sweetish beginning. Sticky, grainy. Somehow strange with not too much bitterness.

Bottle from Snake Off-licence, Lefkoa, Occupied Turkish North of Cyprus . Rated as "Efes Malt". Smooth sweetish beginning. Hints of bitterness, round and smooth. A bit strange grainy in the aftertaste, sessionable with not too much depth and sweetish-grainy hints.

Bottle from Snake Off-licence, Lefkoa, Occupied Turkish North of Cyprus . Nice malty beginning. Hints of grain, not too sweetish. Nice grainy round aftertaste with not too much depth. Nice sessionable Lager.

Bottle from Snake Off-Licence in Lefkoa, Turkish occupied Northern Cyprus . Highly carbonated real ale. Smooth, fresh. Grainy but refreshing, easy to drink, a bit grainy in the aftertaste. Dust, cardboard, but nice. Moderate bitter in the aftertaste. Hints of typical ale aroma with golden grainy hints in the aftertaste! Nice stuff!
Bottle from an - supermarket in Cyprus . Smooth grainy beginning. Full flavour, a bit worthy. Round and fresh, moderate bitter, smooth, round. Nice stuff!!
Bottle from Carrefour in Cyprus . The beer starts neutral smooth. A bit of grain, a bit of sweetish malts. Sessionable, round. Not much bitterness, a bit metallic but very nice.
Bottle from Metro-Supermarket in Larnaca, Cyprus . Neutral watery beginning. Lots of water over a bit of beer. Hints of grain, smooth watery with sweetish hints. Sessionable watery brew!
Can from Carrefour, Larnaka, Cyprus . Smooth neutral grainy beginning. Not too deep, grainy with not much bitterness. Plain metallic in the aftertaste, not too sweetish, sessionable!
Can from a touristy shop in  , Cyprus . Neutral grainy beginning. Hints of metal,quite neutral. Easy to drink with not much bitterness. Smooth, sessionable!

On tap in Cyprus  Awful stuff! The nose is like a toilet someone used for vomitting. The beer starts like old cardboard with metal. Hints of metallic grain, not much bitterness. Awful aftertaste... dont know what happened to this beer - or does it have to taste like this?

On Tap, this year 7.9%.  Nice fresh and grainy sweetish beginning. Easy to drink, fresh and round. Smooth mild, not too sweetish. Round with a nice grainy bitterness. Easy to drink, smooth mild. The yeast is round and fresh, the body soft. Great unfiltered Maibock.
On tap. Smooth sweetish beginning. Grain with a smooth but sweetish body. Not too much bitterness, round but too sweetish with too less bitterness for a Pils. But sessionable.

Sehr florale frische Note. Das Bier startet sehr sffig & hopfenaromatisch. Rund und weich, sehr floral & sffig. Mild grasig mit toller Hopfennote im Nachgeschmack. Tolle Citrus-Tne. Sffig und toll! Der geringe ABV fllt kaum auf.

Fresh fruity nose of sour red currant and goose berries. The beer starts fresh with a nice fruity and very viscous-piney resin texture. Long and intense hop oils. The aftertaste is very complex and intense. The fresh and piney-resin-like hop oils are dominating the picture. The sour fruits are there, red currant and goose berry. Great!

Extreme dark and deep beginning. Caramel, cookies, chocolate, espresso. Lots of depth. The texture is very smooth, velvet, dark caramel, moderate roast. Long roast-smooth malty and not too sweetish chocolate-espresso viscous aftertaste. Fascinating with not too much bitterness and a moderate nice smooth sweetness. Great!

beer_brewer_name: Grfl. von Mengersensche Dampfbrauerei - Schlobrauerei Rheder
review_blob: Smooth and mild beginning. The texture is very soft, the bitterness in the aftertaste moderate. In the aftertaste there is a bit of grainy malty sweetness, that tends to become a bit bready. The body is soft, hints of dust. Easy to drink, very smooth and mild, great sessionable with some nice and smooth grainy parts.

Smooth fresh beginning. Easy to drink with a fresh and mild body. Hints of grain, very crisp and clear. The aftertaste has hints of sweetness, very smooth with not much bitterness. Fascinating mild. Great smooth and highly drinkable and slightly grainy aftertaste. Very nice session-beer!
Sweetish, slightly grainy beginning. Yeast, bready alcohol-free aroma, not too drinkable. Like a liquid full-grain toast. Sweetish-grainy in the aftertaste. Strange.

Very yeasty nose. The beer starts yeasty fresh, nice banana and clove. Very round and fresh, lots of banana, a slightly grainy body that fits in well. The aftertaste is moderate dry-bitter, nice fresh clove, the ripe banana is there together with lots of yeast. Interesting, highly drinkable nice.

Mild-smooth beginning. Very dry with hints of grainy sweetness. Like a Klsch not too much depth, hints of grain and easy to drink. The aftertaste is round and fresh, long and smooth with hints of malty sweetness. Crisp with a nice carbonation. Nice and round.

Slich-limonadiger Antrunk. Das Bier im Hintergrund ist rund, die Limonade schn zitronig ausgewogen. Mild aber nicht zu s, schn sffig. Der Nachgeschmack ist limonadig-ausgeglichen, schne aromatische Zitrone vor mildem Bier. Echt lecker!
Smooth fresh and slightly grainy beginning. Easy to drink, round and smooth. The aftertaste i grainy with a moderate bitterness, very sessionable and easy to drink. Nice.

75cl bottle.  Nice fruity intense quince nose. The quince-perry starts fruity and tart-bitter. A bit mouldy-fruity, very ripe and intense, but not as fresh as the carbonation wants to be. Nice ripe quinces, but the mouldy touch is present. Long intense fruity-sweetish aftertaste with not too much sourness. The mouldy ground aroma is there, still easy to drink with a nice fresh fruity aftertaste. Interesting and highly-drinkble!

Many thanks to Beerhunter111 for sharing!  The beer starts sweetish but round. Smooth and dry malty beginning, not too aromatic. Sessionable Dunkel, not too dry, not too malty, not too bitter. A bit flat in the aromatic, hints of chocolate, moderate bitter in the aftertaste.

Many thanks to Beerhunter111 for sharing!  Intense and roasted sweetish beginning. Sticky, deep. Malty caramel, sweetish malt. Not too much depth, hints of roast. Sweetish Espresso, not much bitterness. Sessionable with too much alcohol. Round and easy to drink - but way too sweet.

Many thanks to Beerhunter111 for this bottle!  Smooth beginning with sourish hints. The brew is malty, hints of sourness, round and roasty. Not much smoke there, more roast on a dry malty basis. The aftertaste is moderate, round and smooth, fresh though.

Many thanks to Beerhunter111 for this bottle!  Smooth and typical sweetish beginning. The beer is round and fresh, sticky sweetish as this style should be. The alcohol is not tasteable, the body is smooth and very sessionable malty with sweetish hints. Nice!
beer_name: Zils-Bru UK Single Hop Amber Scotch Strong Ale

review_blob: Many thanks to Beerhunter111 for sharing!  The beer starts smooth and fresh. Hints of dried yellow fruits, not too much depth. The beer is complex but easy to drink. Smooth, round and refreshing with lots of easy to drink fruits.

Many thanks to Beerunter111 for sharing!  Nice ros colour. The cider starts fresh and fruity. Very nice and round, fresh. On the sweetish side, but very fruity. The apples are nice and "real", no artificial aroma. Long fruity sessionable sweetish fresh aftertaste!

Many thanks to Beerunter111 for sharing!  Nice and fresh beginning. The apples are round and fresh, nice fruitiness with not too much sweetness. The aftertaste is long, fruity fresh. Hints of sourness, not too tart. Nice typical with a smooth sweetish-dry fruity body!
beer_name: Kelterei Krmer Schoppen Odenwlder Apfelwein trb
